Forensic Analyst Weekly Report
Week of June 9–13, 2026

Executive Summary

This week's efforts spanned three core areas of operational and analytical impact. A significant overhaul of the detection engineering pipeline was completed, substantially reducing manual overhead and improving rule governance through automation and GitLab-native workflows. Analyst onboarding support was provided to ensure the incoming team member was successfully integrated into operational tools and environment requirements. Additionally, a formal after action brief was prepared and delivered to branch leadership, communicating observed threat actor tactics, techniques, and procedures (TTPs), lessons learned, and actionable deliverables derived from a completed investigation.

1. Detection Engineering Pipeline Overhaul

Executed a comprehensive redesign of the detection engineering workflow, modernizing the management and lifecycle of detection rules from repository to operational deployment. Key improvements prioritized automation, scalability, and governance.

Scope & Approach
•	Overhauled the end-to-end detection rule management process, consolidating rule lifecycle operations into a centralized repository structure aligned to the operational environment.
•	Significantly reduced manual intervention by leveraging GitLab-native capabilities to automate change tracking, version control, and cross-file dependency management across the detection rule set.
•	Simplified the operational workflow to enable more consistent and repeatable rule deployment, reducing friction between development and production environments.

Community Rule Submission & Merge Gate
•	Implemented a structured merge gate to govern the community rule submission pipeline, ensuring all externally contributed detection rules are validated and checked against the production repository prior to being eligible for merge into the main branch.
•	The merge gate introduces an automated validation layer that enforces rule quality and compatibility standards, reducing the risk of regression or operational impact from untested community-sourced content.
•	This improvement strengthens the integrity of the detection rule library while enabling broader contributor participation in a controlled and auditable manner.

2. New Analyst Onboarding & Integration Support

Provided strategic onboarding support to facilitate the successful integration of an incoming analyst into the team's operational framework and tooling ecosystem.

Onboarding Activities
•	Coordinated with team leads and stakeholders to initiate required account access requests, ensuring the analyst had the necessary permissions to begin contributing across relevant platforms.
•	Conducted an orientation to key SIEM tooling, establishing foundational knowledge of the team's detection and monitoring capabilities to accelerate operational readiness.
•	Facilitated resolution of environment configuration requirements, enabling the analyst to establish a fully operational host forensic environment aligned to mission requirements.

Outcome
•	The analyst achieved the prerequisite access and environmental setup milestones necessary to begin contributing to operational tasks, reducing onboarding lead time and minimizing disruption to ongoing mission activities.

3. After Action Brief — Threat Actor TTP Analysis

Prepared and delivered a segment of a formal after action brief (AAB) to branch leadership, synthesizing findings from a completed investigation into a structured knowledge transfer with lasting organizational value.

Brief Content & Delivery
•	Presented an analysis of threat actor TTPs observed and documented during the course of the investigation, providing leadership with a clear understanding of adversary behaviors, tradecraft, and attack patterns.
•	Communicated key lessons learned derived from the investigation lifecycle, including detection opportunities, analytical approaches, and areas for process refinement.
•	Highlighted actionable deliverables developed as a direct result of the investigation findings, including artifacts and resources made available to the organization for ongoing defensive operations.

Organizational Impact
•	The brief contributed to organizational knowledge management by translating investigative outcomes into reusable intelligence and detection capabilities.
•	Lessons learned were framed to inform future analytic workflows and strengthen the team's collective response posture against similar threat actor activity.

 
